These are essential for usability, safety, and Web Store approval:

Customizable Block List

Let users add or remove sites from the blocked list.

Example: popup.html could have an input + “Add Site” button.

Configurable Delay Timer

Instead of always instant overlay, allow users to set 1–10 second pause before they can click “Continue.”

Makes it feel more like “One Sec.”

Accurate Usage Tracking

Track time spent per site or number of visits per day.

Optionally, track weekly stats for better insights.

Persistent Settings

Store blocked sites, delay time, and stats in chrome.storage.sync (so they sync across devices).

Clean, Intuitive UI

Overlay and popup should look professional: readable fonts, proper spacing, clear buttons.

Privacy Compliance

No data leaves the user’s computer unless you explicitly implement cloud sync.

Web Store reviewers hate extensions that track browsing without explicit consent.

💡 Suggested Order of Feature Implementation Before Web Store:

Custom block list + delay timer

Daily stats tracking + popup UI

Persistent settings via chrome.storage.sync

Clean overlay & popup styling

Optional gamification / motivational prompts